Gentle Knights of the Round Table,
Let us see if the wine is good.
Gentle Knights of the Round Table,
Let us see if the wine is good.
 Let us see, oui-oui-oui;
Let us see, non-non-non;
Let us see if the wine is good.
Let us see, oui-oui-oui;
Let us see, non-non-non;
Let us see if the wine is good.
 If it's good and if it's enjoyable,
I will drink 'til I've had my fill.
If it's good and if it's enjoyable,
I will drink 'til I've had my fill.
 I will drink, oui-oui-oui;
I will drink, non-non-non;
I will drink 'til I've had my fill.
I will drink, oui-oui-oui;
I will drink, non-non-non;
I will drink 'til I've had my fill.
 I'll drink down five or six bottles
With a gal sitting on my lap.
I'll drink down five or six bottles
With a gal sitting on my lap.
 With a gal, oui-oui-oui;
With a gal, non-non-non;
With a gal sitting on my lap.
With a gal, oui-oui-oui;
With a gal, non-non-non;
With a gal sitting on my lap.
 Rat-a-tat – who's that rapping on the door?
I suspect that it is her spouse!
Rat-a-tat – who's that
rapping on the door?
I suspect that it is her spouse!
 I suspect, oui-oui-oui;
I suspect, non-non-non;
I suspect that it is her spouse!
I suspect, oui-oui-oui;
I suspect, non-non-non;
I suspect that it is her spouse!
 If it is, the devil take him
For disturbing me in pleasure sweet!
If it is, the devil take him
For disturbing me in pleasure sweet!
 For disturbing, oui-oui-oui;
For disturbing, non-non-non;
For disturbing me in pleasure sweet.
For disturbing, oui-oui-oui;
For disturbing, non-non-non;
For disturbing me in pleasure sweet.
 When I die, I want to be buried
In a cave where the wine is good.
When I die, I want to be buried
In a cave where the wine is good.
 In a cave, oui-oui-oui;
In a cave, non-non-non;
In a cave where the wine is good.
In a cave, oui-oui-oui;
In a cave, non-non-non;
In a cave where the wine is good.
 'Neath a large cask, with both feet upon the wall,
and my head right beneath the bung.
'Neath a large cask, with both feet upon the wall, and my head right beneath the bung.
 And my head, oui-oui-oui;
And my head, non-non-non;
And my head right beneath the bung.
And my head, oui-oui-oui;
And my head, non-non-non;
And my head right beneath the bung.
 And, if the bung pops out,
I will drink 'til I feel my face no more.
And, if the bung pops out,
I will drink 'til I feel my face no more.
 I will drink, oui-oui-oui;
I will drink, non-non-non;
I will drink 'til I feel my face no more.
I will drink, oui-oui-oui;
I will drink, non-non-non;
I will drink 'til I feel my face no more.
 And the country's four biggest drunkards
Will carry me wrapped in my shroud.
And the country's four biggest drunkards
Will carry me wrapped in my shroud.
 Will carry, oui-oui-oui;
Will carry, non-non-non;
Will carry me wrapped in my shroud.
Will carry, oui-oui-oui;
Will carry, non-non-non;
Will carry me wrapped in my shroud.
 On my tomb, I want to be recorded:
"Here asleep the king of drunks lies."
On my tomb, I want to be recorded:
"Here asleep the king of drunks lies."
 "Here asleep," oui-oui-oui;
"Here asleep," non-non-non;
"Here asleep the king of drunks lies."
"Here asleep," oui-oui-oui;
"Here asleep," non-non-non;
"Here asleep the king of drunks lies."
 Now, the moral of this long story
Is (to strive) to drink while you're still alive.
Now, the moral of this long story
Is (to strive) to drink while you're still alive.
 Is to drink (or "Is to strive"), oui-oui-oui;
Is to drink (Is to strive), non-non-non;
Is (to strive) to drink while you're still alive.
Is to drink (Is to strive), oui-oui-oui;
Is to drink (Is to strive), non-non-non;
Is (to strive) to drink while you're still alive.

